1
00:00:00,789 --> 00:00:04,880
Trading with patterns is an essential component
of technical analysis.

2
00:00:04,880 --> 00:00:10,780
This means that you need to shift your focus
on price action and what the pattern shows.

3
00:00:10,780 --> 00:00:14,950
All markets, regardless of type, have one
thing in common.

4
00:00:14,950 --> 00:00:17,560
That is, they all consolidate in ranges.

5
00:00:17,560 --> 00:00:19,190
A lot.

6
00:00:19,190 --> 00:00:23,820
Therefore, one of the most common chart patterns
are triangles.

7
00:00:23,820 --> 00:00:29,500
The triangle pattern is a specific figure
formed on the price chart, typically identified

8
00:00:29,500 --> 00:00:34,230
when the tops and the bottoms of the price
action are moving toward each other like the

9
00:00:34,230 --> 00:00:36,170
sides of a triangle.

10
00:00:36,170 --> 00:00:41,750
When the upper and the lower level of a triangle
interact, traders expect an eventual breakout

11
00:00:41,750 --> 00:00:42,750
from that area.

12
00:00:42,750 --> 00:00:49,450
As such, many breakout traders use triangle
formations for identifying breakout entry

13
00:00:49,450 --> 00:00:50,450
points.

14
00:00:50,450 --> 00:00:55,070
There are different kinds of triangles that
can be seen on a chart.

15
00:00:55,070 --> 00:01:00,540
In this video we’ll take a closer look at
the ascending triangle pattern and the corresponding

16
00:01:00,540 --> 00:01:02,320
trade setups.

17
00:01:02,320 --> 00:01:06,360
Once you are equipped with this knowledge,
you should be able to add a triangle trading

18
00:01:06,360 --> 00:01:10,560
strategy to your trade setup arsenal.

19
00:01:10,560 --> 00:01:16,540
The ascending triangle formation is a continuation
pattern and as the name suggests it has the

20
00:01:16,540 --> 00:01:18,280
shape of a triangle.

21
00:01:18,280 --> 00:01:23,820
The ascending triangle is also known as the
bullish triangle because it leads to a bullish

22
00:01:23,820 --> 00:01:25,350
breakout.

23
00:01:25,350 --> 00:01:30,290
This is how the ascending triangle looks like:
The first element of this price pattern is

24
00:01:30,290 --> 00:01:34,110
an upward slope followed by a flat top.

25
00:01:34,110 --> 00:01:40,740
This shows that the market has tried multiple
times to break the resistance top but it couldn’t.

26
00:01:40,740 --> 00:01:44,500
Hence, we have developed a resistance line.

27
00:01:44,500 --> 00:01:51,130
The second element of the ascending triangle
is a rising trend line moving upwards.

28
00:01:51,130 --> 00:01:53,930
This is what makes the pattern bullish.

29
00:01:53,930 --> 00:01:58,900
Now, all continuation patterns need to have
a context of a trend.

30
00:01:58,900 --> 00:02:04,740
In the case of the bullish ascending triangle,
we need to have a previous uptrend to support

31
00:02:04,740 --> 00:02:06,080
the breakout.

32
00:02:06,080 --> 00:02:11,450
Now that you learned how the ascending formation
looks like i want to share with you several

33
00:02:11,450 --> 00:02:15,840
important things that I’ve learned from
trading the bullish triangle.

34
00:02:15,840 --> 00:02:21,790
First, on a price chart, the triangle pattern
will rarely have a perfect shape.

35
00:02:21,790 --> 00:02:27,419
Often times you’ll see an ascending wedge
pattern which will break the resistance line

36
00:02:27,419 --> 00:02:30,330
but have no real momentum behind the breakout.

37
00:02:30,330 --> 00:02:36,969
Other times, the pattern will develop spiky
bars that will lead to false breakouts.

38
00:02:36,969 --> 00:02:38,620
There is no perfect pattern.

39
00:02:38,620 --> 00:02:41,709
What's the first thing you see in this chart?

40
00:02:41,709 --> 00:02:44,299
That's right, the pattern is not perfect.

41
00:02:44,299 --> 00:02:49,790
I remember how I would read a book on a specific
chart pattern and then when i would go in

42
00:02:49,790 --> 00:02:53,260
the market, I could never find an exact match.

43
00:02:53,260 --> 00:02:58,010
For example, in this chart, notice how the
highs are not aligned perfectly.

44
00:02:58,010 --> 00:03:03,609
But, notice how the stock breaks through the
uptrend line, only to go higher.

45
00:03:03,609 --> 00:03:08,310
So don’t search only for perfect triangles.

46
00:03:08,310 --> 00:03:14,519
Also, you really need to think in terms of
what it’s going on behind the scene.

47
00:03:14,519 --> 00:03:19,059
You don’t just have to look at the price,
but also try to read what the market participants

48
00:03:19,059 --> 00:03:20,290
are doing.

49
00:03:20,290 --> 00:03:25,359
When the price is moving up, it starts to
develop the classical higher lows.

50
00:03:25,359 --> 00:03:30,279
For whatever the reasons, the buyers may become
a little bit more aggressive with each new

51
00:03:30,279 --> 00:03:32,120
successive higher low.

52
00:03:32,120 --> 00:03:37,349
Or, we can say that the sellers aren’t too
aggressive when the market turns down inside

53
00:03:37,349 --> 00:03:39,879
the ascending triangle chart pattern.

54
00:03:39,879 --> 00:03:44,359
Whichever alternative you prefer, that is
what it’s causing the triangle price formation

55
00:03:44,359 --> 00:03:45,809
to develop.

56
00:03:45,809 --> 00:03:51,069
When we reach the climax point of the triangle
where the price has nowhere to go, that’s

57
00:03:51,069 --> 00:03:55,739
the moment when you should anticipate a breakout.

58
00:03:55,739 --> 00:03:58,939
The location of the pattern is also important!

59
00:03:58,939 --> 00:04:04,479
If the triangle pattern is inside of a big
trading range, then the solid resistance level

60
00:04:04,479 --> 00:04:07,019
might not be that significant.

61
00:04:07,019 --> 00:04:12,189
If you pay attention at this chart, you’ll
notice the triangle pattern, but the problem

62
00:04:12,189 --> 00:04:18,650
is that it develops inside a big trading range,
so even if there is a small breakout, the

63
00:04:18,650 --> 00:04:22,530
upward movement is restricted by this other
resistance.

64
00:04:22,530 --> 00:04:29,700
However, if the ascending triangle price formation
develops in the middle of a bullish trend

65
00:04:29,700 --> 00:04:32,700
that would add more weight to the pattern.

66
00:04:32,700 --> 00:04:37,000
When the ascending triangle develops within
a trend then we’re going to be interested

67
00:04:37,000 --> 00:04:42,650
in buying the breakout, like in this example.

68
00:04:42,650 --> 00:04:48,230
Regardless of their location, during a trend,
ascending triangles are bullish patterns that

69
00:04:48,230 --> 00:04:50,180
indicate accumulation.

70
00:04:50,180 --> 00:04:55,380
The higher lows in the pattern are a clue
that buyers are not letting their position

71
00:04:55,380 --> 00:05:01,780
go at lower prices as the pattern makes higher
lows.

72
00:05:01,780 --> 00:05:06,690
Another important tip is that you need to
have a clear resistance level, with a series

73
00:05:06,690 --> 00:05:10,930
of highs occurring at or near the same price.

74
00:05:10,930 --> 00:05:17,380
You don't want to have one or two peaks, because
it might be a swing high or double top.

75
00:05:17,380 --> 00:05:23,380
There needs to be a number of clear attempts
by the bulls that go nowhere with the price.

76
00:05:23,380 --> 00:05:28,440
Once the triangle breakout happens you need
to see a pick-up in volume that will result

77
00:05:28,440 --> 00:05:30,630
in a nice long trade.

78
00:05:30,630 --> 00:05:36,460
The next thing you want to see in a breakout
is for volume to accelerate on the move higher.

79
00:05:36,460 --> 00:05:40,650
This does not mean the volume on the breakout
has to be the highest over the last 24 hours

80
00:05:40,650 --> 00:05:41,920
or something.

81
00:05:41,920 --> 00:05:45,590
It just means you need to see some acceleration
to the upside.

82
00:05:45,590 --> 00:05:51,490
The key point is you want to see buyers participate
in the move to increase the likelihood of

83
00:05:51,490 --> 00:05:52,490
follow-through.

84
00:05:52,490 --> 00:05:57,770
How do you trade an ascending triangle pattern?

85
00:05:57,770 --> 00:06:03,490
The classic method is to buy the breakout
once you have had 3 or more touches with volume.

86
00:06:03,490 --> 00:06:07,680
Now, you have a few choices of where to enter.

87
00:06:07,680 --> 00:06:13,560
The first option is to buy on the highest
high after three or more tops.

88
00:06:13,560 --> 00:06:18,580
The potential issue with this approach is
that the price could fail and is still either

89
00:06:18,580 --> 00:06:23,550
developing the ascending triangle or you are
caught in a bull trap.

90
00:06:23,550 --> 00:06:28,990
The main problem with triangles, and chart
patterns in general, is the potential for

91
00:06:28,990 --> 00:06:30,830
false breakouts.

92
00:06:30,830 --> 00:06:36,300
The price may move out of the pattern only
to move back into it, or the price may even

93
00:06:36,300 --> 00:06:38,990
proceed to break out the other side.

94
00:06:38,990 --> 00:06:46,050
A pattern may need to be redrawn several times
as the price edges past the trend lines but

95
00:06:46,050 --> 00:06:50,550
fails to generate any momentum in the breakout
direction.

96
00:06:50,550 --> 00:06:53,840
What I prefer is to look at pivot points.

97
00:06:53,840 --> 00:06:59,840
I like to wait for a key pivot point resistance
level to be breached and then place a buy

98
00:06:59,840 --> 00:07:03,530
order slightly above this level.

99
00:07:03,530 --> 00:07:09,170
The potential issue with this approach is
you are exposed to more risk as you are buying

100
00:07:09,170 --> 00:07:12,890
at higher levels with greater downside exposure.

101
00:07:12,890 --> 00:07:19,070
But, this will eliminate a lot of false breakouts,
which will occur a lot.

102
00:07:19,070 --> 00:07:23,430
That’s why I like to add a safety net by
using pivot points.

103
00:07:23,430 --> 00:07:29,200
So, if you pay attention at this example,
we have the upper trend line, with higher

104
00:07:29,200 --> 00:07:34,330
lows, the clear resistance level, and the
breakout.

105
00:07:34,330 --> 00:07:41,120
But, in real time, as we don’t know if the
breakout is real or not, we wait for the price

106
00:07:41,120 --> 00:07:48,060
to consolidate above this pivot level, as
a confirmation of the breakout of the pattern.

107
00:07:48,060 --> 00:07:53,120
Once the price consolidated above, we can
safely search for long entries.

108
00:07:53,120 --> 00:08:19,190
Here are other examples of ascending triangles
breakouts, with pivot points confirmation.

109
00:08:19,190 --> 00:08:23,419
Another approach is to buy inside of the triangle.

110
00:08:23,419 --> 00:08:28,710
Once you see the pattern setting up, you can
wait for a touch of the uptrend line and then

111
00:08:28,710 --> 00:08:30,730
place a long entry.

112
00:08:30,730 --> 00:08:36,559
The benefits with this approach are that you
can place a tighter stop since you are closer

113
00:08:36,559 --> 00:08:42,769
to the demand line (support), this also gives
you a potential profit before the actual breakout.

114
00:08:42,769 --> 00:08:48,639
The downside to this approach is you could
wait a longer time for the move through the

115
00:08:48,639 --> 00:08:52,760
top of the triangle, in a possible consolidation
phase.

116
00:08:52,760 --> 00:08:56,970
This is a more advanced technique, and the
most important thing is that you need to have

117
00:08:56,970 --> 00:08:59,350
a clear uptrend.

118
00:08:59,350 --> 00:09:04,100
When you spot an ascending triangle on the
chart, you should be prepared to catch a bullish

119
00:09:04,100 --> 00:09:08,160
price move equal to at least the size of the
triangle.

120
00:09:08,160 --> 00:09:13,720
A profit target can be estimated based on
the height of the triangle added from the

121
00:09:13,720 --> 00:09:16,089
breakout price.

122
00:09:16,089 --> 00:09:22,020
The white lines correspond to the size of
the triangle and its potential target, which

123
00:09:22,020 --> 00:09:24,819
is typically a 1:1 measured move.

124
00:09:24,819 --> 00:09:31,930
So, the profit target for the setup is the
distance of the triangle added to the top.

125
00:09:31,930 --> 00:09:36,720
Regarding stops, there are multiple areas
where you can place your stop orders.

126
00:09:36,720 --> 00:09:42,470
First, you can place the stop order beneath
the uptrend line.

127
00:09:42,470 --> 00:09:45,829
You can also use the low of the breakout candle.

128
00:09:45,829 --> 00:09:51,870
If the price is able to break out, you can
place your stop below the low of the candlestick.

129
00:09:51,870 --> 00:09:58,250
This way if the price reverses, you are not
waiting until the uptrend line is breached.

130
00:09:58,250 --> 00:10:01,329
This way you can keep more of your gains.

131
00:10:01,329 --> 00:10:08,120
Also, keep in mind, while ascending triangles
provide a profit target, that target is just

132
00:10:08,120 --> 00:10:09,750
an estimate.

133
00:10:09,750 --> 00:10:14,699
The price may far exceed that target, or fail
to reach it.

134
00:10:14,699 --> 00:10:19,480
This is why, using proper risk-reward ratios
is mandatory.

135
00:10:19,480 --> 00:10:25,290
Otherwise, the risk is that the triangle pattern
will transform into something else and will

136
00:10:25,290 --> 00:10:31,540
invalidate the reason you have entered in
that particular trade in the first place.

137
00:10:31,540 --> 00:10:35,589
If you got any value from this and learned
something new, don’t forget to subscribe,

138
00:10:35,589 --> 00:10:39,680
hit the bell icon and leave us a like to show
your support.

